div.p:
Lastly, as he was a Iudge, he shook his hands from holding of bribes, as Isaiah expresses it, Chap. 33. verse 15. The word signifies Volam the palm, the hollow of the hand, which others who sell courtesies hold out to receive their gratuities; 
                        〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                      (a speech too proverbial in taking of fees) This he shook, which of old was a Symbol of hatred or disdain.
